## Description {#details}

This class provides support for representing a failure result, or a valid value of type <code>T</code>.

This allows for integrating with <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/logicalresult">LogicalResult</a>, while also providing a value on the success path.

Definition at line 76 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/support/logicalresult-h">LogicalResult.h</a>.

Allow constructing from a <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/logicalresult">LogicalResult</a>.

The result <em>must</em> be a failure. Success results should use a proper instance of type <code>T</code>.
